. As a by-product of this expressivity, we show that verifying properties of transformers is provably intractable (i.e. EXPSPACE-complete).","submitter_user":"aphaelion","user_is_author":false,"tags":["ai"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/hzhyw9","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/hzhyw9/transformers_are_inherently_succinct"},{"short_id":"bwg33l","created_at":"2026-04-25T15:10:21.000-05:00","title":"My Homemade PBX","url":"https://wandel.ca/homepage/pbx.html","score":16,"flags":0,"comment_count":4,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"thomas536","user_is_author":false,"tags":["hardware"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/bwg33l","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/bwg33l/my_homemade_pbx"},{"short_id":"uiqamk","created_at":"2026-04-25T14:48:15.000-05:00","title":"Hyper-DERP: C++/io_uring DERP relay - Same throughput as Tailscale's derper, half the cores","url":"https://hyper-derp.dev/blog/hyper-derp-announcement/","score":16,"flags":0,"comment_count":1,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"knl","user_is_author":false,"tags":["performance"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/uiqamk","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/uiqamk/hyper_derp_c_io_uring_derp_relay_same"},{"short_id":"spm1cr","created_at":"2026-04-25T14:40:00.000-05:00","title":"Revocation of X.509 certificates","url":"https://blog.apnic.net/2026/04/24/revocation-of-x-509-certificates/","score":2,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"raymii","user_is_author":false,"tags":["security"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/spm1cr","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/spm1cr/revocation_x_509_certificates"},{"short_id":"88pksu","created_at":"2026-04-25T13:24:40.000-05:00","title":"Linux May Drop Old Network Drivers Now That AI-Driven Bug Reports Are Causing A Burden","url":"https://www.phoronix.com/news/Linux-Old-Network-AI","score":26,"flags":0,"comment_count":20,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"